  "texts": [
    "At epoch e and for sample s, the gradient norm is computed as:g e,s = P j=1 ∂L e,s ∂θ j 2 2,(1)where θ j denotes the j th trainable parameter in the network and P is the total number of parameters.",
    "These norms are stored in a matrix G ∈ R E×N, where E is the number of epochs.",
    "The importance score of a sample s is then defined as:I(s) = 1 E E e=1 g e,s.",
    "(2) Important Sample SelectionThe goal of sample selection is to find a metric that orders the samples according to their importance, and to use that metric to select the most relevant ones for training the model.",
    "In this work, the metric we consider is the importance score based on the gradient, defined in (2).The selection of the most p% important samples thus corresponds to the set:S * p = arg max S⊂D;|S|≤k s∈S I(s),(3)where |S| denotes the cardinality of S and k = p 100 × n is the number of samples corresponding to p%."
